rComments: Atanasoski is one of my favorite professors. She is clear and easy to follow and makes classes interesting. She is open to input and a good person to talk to during office hours. Thoroughly enjoyed this class!

WINTER 2011: The assignments in the class syllabus (i.e. the films and text) were extremely interesting. However, Atanasoski's lectures were completely unnecessary as they were exact reiterations of the readings assigned.
